For this task, I used a digital design tool to create an infographic titled "Digital Literacy for Students". The design highlights three key areas: useful digital tools, safe internet practices, and professional online presence, with an additional banner on email etiquette. Each section uses distinct colors and icons to make the information visually engaging and easy to understand. For example, the “Useful Digital Tools” section features icons for note-taking apps, cloud storage, and productivity software, while “Safe Internet Practices” emphasizes strong passwords, privacy settings, and phishing awareness. The "Professional Online Presence" section illustrates how to maintain a clean profile, use a professional photo, and build networks responsibly. Finally, the email etiquette banner reinforces polite greetings, clarity, and tone in communication.
One interesting aspect of this project was balancing clarity with visual appeal. It was challenging to condense complex ideas into concise text and pair them with simple icons without losing meaning. However, this process taught me how effective visual communication can be in promoting digital literacy and professional online behavior.
